  "text": "The Java ClassLoader delegation chain in OpenJDK follows a parent-first delegation model that spans both Java and C++ layers:\n\n1. **Java Layer - ClassLoader (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java, line 534)**: The `protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method implements the core parent-first delegation pattern. It first checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass()`, then delegates to the parent class loader before attempting to find the class itself.\n\n2. **Java Layer - BuiltinClassLoader (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java, line 89)**: The `BuiltinClassLoader` class extends `SecureClassLoader` and serves as the base class for the three built-in loaders. It implements module-aware delegation and class path searching.\n\n3. **Java Layer - ClassLoaders (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java, line 45)**: The `ClassLoaders` utility class creates and manages the three built-in class loaders:\n   - `BootClassLoader` (line 131): Loads classes from boot modules, delegates to native bootstrap loader\n   - `PlatformClassLoader` (line 146): Loads platform module classes, parent is BootClassLoader\n   - `AppClassLoader` (line 161): Loads application classes from the class path, parent is PlatformClassLoader\n\n4. **C++ Layer - ClassLoader (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp, line 1141)**: The `InstanceKlass* ClassLoader::load_class()` method implements native class loading and file I/O operations for reading class files.\n\n5. **C++ Layer - SystemDictionary (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp, line 78 and systemDictionary.cpp, line 332)**: The `SystemDictionary` class acts as a global cache for all loaded classes. The `resolve_or_fail()` method handles class resolution with synchronization and error checking. It manages the class cache per ClassLoaderData and implements the dictionary lookup for loaded classes.\n\nThe delegation chain works as follows: Java code calls `loadClass()` → delegates to parent → eventually reaches native layer → `ClassLoader::load_class()` reads the class file → `SystemDictionary::resolve_or_fail()` caches and returns the loaded class back through the chain."
}

